isnull()

Description
    bool isnull(mixed $var [, bool $strict = TRUE])
	Performs a number of tests upon the parameter, $v, to determine whether it is null.

Parameters
    var
		A variable, $var, of any type may be passed to the function.
	strict
		Boolean value.  If FALSE, the function will pass $var to PHP's function, is_null().  Processing otherwise proceeds through the current function.
	
Return Values
    Returns a boolean value.  The value is TRUE if the variable meets the EngineCMS definitions for a NULL special value, described in the Notes 
	section.  The value is otherwise FALSE.
	
Examples
    <?php
		...
		if (!isnull($errorMsg)) {
			return $errorMsg;
		}
		else {
			return TRUE;
		}
		...
	?>

Notes
	EngineCMS defines a null variable as one that:
	1. Is of string type and equal to the value "null";
	2. is identical to the special type NULL.

	There is only one value of type null , and that is the case-insensitive keyword NULL.  View http://www.php.net/manual/en/language.types.null.php 
	for more information regarding the NULL special value.
	
See Also
	is_empty()